file?language=EN>Angrist</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>9/5/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>5:33:02 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Soloing</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Just wanted to know if anyone has tried Soloing after lvl 39 and have they found it effective or no. Last night I soloed the guards in WC and made  a bub and a half in less than 2 hrs. Not the greatest exp but not too shabby. Of course I had the occasional breeze/clarity and SoW when someone was nice enough to pass it out.<br>
  Just curious thats all<br>
<br>
<br>
Angrist Soulstealer <br>
39th Dark Knight of Hate<br>
</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#E5E5E6><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uslickem.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SlickEm</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>9/5/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>5:59:10 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Soloing</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">First I have to say, 1 and a half bubbles xp in 2 hours is great for your lvl.<br>
<br>
I had tried soloing a few times in my pre 50 days... I am not sure if i was poor at controlling a pet or at coordinating my spells, but it was horribly inefficient.  However, the other day (I now have my lvl 52 summon pet spell) I went to burning woods to try to solo some undeads.  After a bit of experimenting and practicing I started getting the hang of things.  Man, it was great fun, and quite efficient as well!  For my lvl there are many low and medium undead blues in that zone, so never a shortage of pulls.  Also the pathing is such that the mob doesn't end up moving to far from your original pull spot after being feared.<br>
<br>
As for good xp... i gained about a quarter bub in 52 in 90 minutes(approx).  If i compare that when I am in a karnors group the xp is about the same.  Of course when alone you always run the risk of getting jumped when low health/mana or fizzling at a bad time and not being able to keep the mob off you. With a group you can recover, alone you are toast.<br>
<br>
I would suggest doing this if you have a limited time on... like under 2 hours or something.</font><P> ----------- <br>Ralanan Blackened<br>52nd Human Reaver<br><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#D5D4D5><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/beqasylum.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kaedianravenblade>Kaedian Ravenblade</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>9/5/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>7:04:17 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Soloing</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Soloing from 39-41 so far has meant sticking to sg's and griff's on the mainland [sporadic spawns] or breaking the ec rangers which isn't as hard as one might think.  Otherwise I head to OT and stick to plants and berzerkers with a cat or two if the others arent around.  Safer then anywhere else and the zone seems made for fear kiting especially if you stick to the right of the clay golem, you can keep the mobs in front of the city with minimal effort.  Exp was noticeable in 39 and again in 41, 40 no matter where you are or what you do, sucks to no end, though exp rolled in a ledge group there since I never stopped pulling.  [try to get an enchanter, healer and nuker, with you as main tank you'll rip them apart and clarity keeps all of you at 80%-fm at all times] <br>
